---- Changes since 1.090 ----
Added an option to change the user's MySQL password at the same time, assuming that the MySQL Database module has been setup properly.
---- Changes since 1.130 ----
When using PAM to change passwords, restrictions on quality and length are now enforced by Usermin calling the PAM libraries in the correct way.
---- Changes since 1.150 ----
Added a configuration option to use MD5 password encryption, which is enabled by default on Linux systems.
---- Changes since 1.640 ----
Added a tab for entering an offsite password recovery address.
